column15:
20/Nov/20 1:24 PM;557058:8ec6fd0e-6ea4-4b8b-bb91-5ec1726a4ece;[~accountid:557058:09cf04a4-0278-4b1d-8e0d-79b1d4ce16b9] No we don’t Gill.. For the Phase 1 summary message we compile the message from ECF Scanner when the gun signals to ECF scanner that the run is PICKED- so no change to gun needed.
 
(For Phase 2- the expanded messages- we *will* need Mobico as the gun needs to raise the new extra signals  back to ECF scanner for us to publish to Azure )
